    <item>
      <title>Zoe&#39;s Tale</title>
      <link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2018/10/11/zoes-tale/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 11 Oct 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2018/10/11/zoes-tale/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;cover-image&#34;&gt;
                &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;2102600&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2102600.zoes-tale&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/zoes-tale.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
            &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In a nutshell, Zoe&amp;rsquo;s Tale is The Last Colony told from Zoe&amp;rsquo;s point of view.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It definitely has a different feel to it than the rest of the Old Man&amp;rsquo;s War books, matching the idea that it was written by a teenage girl (having never been one, I can&amp;rsquo;t guarantee the accuracy, but it worked for me).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>The Last Colony</title>
      <link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2018/09/26/the-last-colony/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 26 Sep 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2018/09/26/the-last-colony/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;cover-image&#34;&gt;
                &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;8180987&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8180987.the-last-colony&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/the-last-colony.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
            &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After John&amp;rsquo;s story in &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;51964&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/51964.old-mans-war&#34;&gt;Old Man&amp;#39;s War&lt;/a&gt; and Jane&amp;rsquo;s (to some extent) in &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;239399&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/239399.the-ghost-brigades&#34;&gt;The Ghost Brigades&lt;/a&gt;, this time around we get both of them. They&amp;rsquo;re together now and raising Zoë (how&amp;rsquo;s that for a complicated family), when they&amp;rsquo;re tapped to head an entirely new colony planet Roanoke&amp;ndash;with the first city named Croatoan. Also&amp;hellip; why would they even agree to that?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I mean&amp;hellip; come on. Either no one knows the history behind the names&amp;ndash;in which case why in the world would they be using them&amp;ndash;or they do&amp;ndash;in which case why in the world would you choose &lt;em&gt;that&lt;/em&gt; to name your new colony. Granted, they turn out to want it to be lost, but still. It&amp;rsquo;s a bit annoying.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>The Ghost Brigades</title>
