      <pubDate>Sat, 08 Sep 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2018/09/08/the-ghost-brigades/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;cover-image&#34;&gt;
                &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;239399&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/239399.the-ghost-brigades&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/the-ghost-brigades.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
            &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After I read &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;51964&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/51964.old-mans-war&#34;&gt;Old Man&amp;#39;s War&lt;/a&gt;, I went looking for the sequels. While on paper &lt;a data-goodreads-type=&#34;book&#34; data-goodreads-id=&#34;239399&#34; href=&#34;https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/239399.the-ghost-brigades&#34;&gt;The Ghost Brigades&lt;/a&gt; is the second in the series, it&amp;rsquo;s surprisingly different.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We get a lot more of a look into the CDF and specifically Special Forces, which was something that was interesting from the first book.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
